# Selector Output - beyond-de-giorgi / run-005

## Full Ranking

1. Chain 01 - Critical Element Program With Host-Space Freeze And Rigidity Admission
2. Chain 02 - Helical-Triad Symbol Route
3. Chain 03 - Tensor Stretching And Pressure-Hessian Route
4. Chain 04 - Local Beltrami Deficit To Geometric Criterion Bridge

## Why These Three Make The Strongest Portfolio

The selected portfolio is Chains 01, 02, and 03.

Chain 01 stays in because it is the highest-upside route in the run and the only branch that can turn a successful audit into a true compactness-rigidity program rather than a local mechanism memo. Its failure mode is also useful: the chain is disciplined enough to say whether the first fatal break is extraction, formulation, definability of the rigidity quantity, or non-coercivity.

Chain 02 stays in because it is the cleanest adversarial test of genuinely Navier-Stokes-specific algebra. It attacks the Tao screen at the exact Leray-symbol and helical-triad level, so even a negative result is informative: it can show that the exact triad geometry becomes cosmetic after honest summation or localization. That makes it both sharply differentiated from Chain 01 and high value on failure.

Chain 03 stays in because it preserves the strongest pressure-adjacent live lead without sliding back into the dead coefficient-shrinkage architecture. It is materially different from Chain 02: the unit of attack is not Fourier triads but the full stretching mechanism `S omega . omega` together with pressure-Hessian debt. It is also likely to produce a calibrated obstruction even if it does not promote to proposition scale, which makes it a strong third slot.

## Why Chain 04 Was Not Selected

Chain 04 is the best surviving geometry reboot, but it is the weakest of the four on expected value. Its first likely breaks are transport persistence, localization debt, and outside-region strain freedom, which means it is more exposed to dying before it reaches a criterion-scale statement. It is genuinely different, but the selected set already achieves strong diversity across global compactness, exact symbolic algebra, and tensorial stretching analysis while keeping a better balance of upside and useful failure output.

## Selection Notes By Rank

### 1. Chain 01

Best ceiling in the portfolio. It has the most theorem-shaped success mode and the most disciplined obstruction taxonomy.

### 2. Chain 02

Best direct test of whether exact NS interaction geometry contains a Tao-sensitive gain. It is narrow enough to audit cleanly and still valuable if the answer is negative.

### 3. Chain 03

Best pressure-adjacent route still alive after earlier eliminations. It engages the central stretching bottleneck directly and should still return a useful non-coercivity diagnosis if it fails.

### 4. Chain 04

Most concrete geometry variant, but also the most vulnerable to persistence and nonlocal-debt failure before earning a portable theorem gap or criterion-scale output.

